    <item>
      <title>Alternator Charging for Portable Power Stations</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/alternator-charging-for-power-stations/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/alternator-charging-for-power-stations/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Alternator charging is often the fastest way to stabilize portable power in real travel routines.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why It Matters&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;why-it-matters&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#why-it-matters&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A modest battery with fast alternator recovery can outperform a larger battery with weak replenishment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>How Many Watt-Hours Do I Need in a Van?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-many-watt-hours-do-i-need/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-many-watt-hours-do-i-need/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Sizing your system starts with daily behavior, not product marketing. Track real device use first, then choose capacity.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Practical Sizing Method&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;practical-sizing-method&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#practical-sizing-method&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;List daily loads (laptop, router, lights, fan, charging).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Estimate hours used per load.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Build a conservative daily total and add margin.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Match station size to both usage and recharge reality.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Diagram placeholder: Daily load worksheet and margin model.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Portable Power vs Full Electrical Build</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/portable-power-vs-full-electrical-build/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/portable-power-vs-full-electrical-build/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This decision should follow your use pattern, not online hype. Portable systems reduce install risk; fixed systems improve integration and scaling.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;When Portable Power Wins&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;when-portable-power-wins&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#when-portable-power-wins&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Portable stations are often best for early-stage builders, remote workers with moderate loads, and people who need power immediately.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Solar Input Explained for Portable Power Stations</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/solar-input-explained-for-power-stations/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/solar-input-explained-for-power-stations/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Solar input is useful, but it is only reliable when panel sizing, weather assumptions, and charge windows are realistic.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Core Concepts&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;core-concepts&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#core-concepts&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Input limits, panel voltage/current matching, and harvest variability drive outcomes more than headline panel wattage.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Budget Kitchen Setup for Van Life</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/budget-kitchen-setup-for-van-life/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/budget-kitchen-setup-for-van-life/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A practical kitchen cuts food costs and keeps road life sustainable.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Core Setup&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;core-setup&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#core-setup&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Two-burner stove&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;One pan + one pot + prep knife&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Dry pantry bins and simple cleanup flow&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What to Skip at First&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-to-skip-at-first&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-to-skip-at-first&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Large permanent installs without real usage data&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Single-purpose gadgets that consume storage&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Read next:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Budget Van Electrical: Simple vs DIY</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/budget-van-electrical-simple-vs-diy/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/budget-van-electrical-simple-vs-diy/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The right electrical strategy depends on your actual usage, not social media build standards.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Simple System (Power Station)&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;simple-system-power-station&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#simple-system-power-station&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Best if you want fast setup, low risk, and minimal wiring. Cost is predictable and troubleshooting is easier.&#xA;We’re keeping this high-level—no wiring instructions here. For installs, follow manufacturer guidance or work with a qualified installer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>How Much Solar Do You Need in a Van?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-much-solar-do-you-need-in-a-van/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-much-solar-do-you-need-in-a-van/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Most people should estimate usage first, then choose solar. Start with a daily load list in watt-hours.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Quick Sizing Rule&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;quick-sizing-rule&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#quick-sizing-rule&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Light use: 200W&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Moderate daily use: 300W-400W&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Heavy remote work + fridge: 500W+&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Then match battery capacity to at least one day of use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>How to Start Van Life on a Budget</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-to-start-van-life-on-a-budget/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-to-start-van-life-on-a-budget/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting van life on a budget is mostly about sequencing. People overspend when they buy comfort upgrades before core systems.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Phase 1: Buy the Right Van&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;phase-1-buy-the-right-van&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#phase-1-buy-the-right-van&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A reliable used van with service history beats a newer van you cannot afford to maintain. Budget for an inspection and first-month repairs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Portable Power Stations vs Full Electrical Build</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/portable-power-stations-vs-full-electrical-build/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/portable-power-stations-vs-full-electrical-build/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This decision controls budget, build timeline, and failure risk.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Power Station Wins If&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;power-station-wins-if&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#power-station-wins-if&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You need power quickly.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Your loads are moderate.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You prefer lower install risk.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;DIY System Wins If&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;diy-system-wins-if&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#diy-system-wins-if&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You run high-watt appliances daily.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You want deep integration and maximum control.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You can design safe electrical systems or hire help.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Practical Recommendation&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;practical-recommendation&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#practical-recommendation&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Start with a quality station, then move to fixed electrical when your daily usage data proves you need it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Tools You’ll Actually Use in a First Build</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The fastest way to overspend on a build is buying every tool recommended online.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Buy First&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;buy-first&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#buy-first&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Drill/driver combo&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Jigsaw + quality blades&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Crimper + multimeter&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;PPE and measuring tools&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Borrow or Rent&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;borrow-or-rent&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#borrow-or-rent&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Specialty saws&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Rare-use heavy tools&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why This Matters&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;why-this-matters&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#why-this-matters&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tool quality affects safety and finish quality, but tool count does not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Van Internet: What Actually Works Off-Grid</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/van-internet-what-actually-works-off-grid/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/van-internet-what-actually-works-off-grid/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Reliable van internet comes from layered redundancy, not one magic device.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Baseline Setup&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;baseline-setup&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#baseline-setup&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Primary hotspot with external antenna support&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Secondary carrier or tether backup&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Mounting and cable routing that protects signal quality&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Common Mistakes&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;common-mistakes&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#common-mistakes&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Chasing theoretical max speeds&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Using only one network&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Ignoring power draw of network hardware&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Read next:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Ventilation Mistakes New Van Lifers Make</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/ventilation-mistakes-new-van-lifers-make/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/ventilation-mistakes-new-van-lifers-make/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Bad airflow causes more daily frustration than most first-time builders expect.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Mistake 1: No Crossflow Plan&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;mistake-1-no-crossflow-plan&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#mistake-1-no-crossflow-plan&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A roof fan alone is not enough. Pair extraction with side-window intake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
